Name: 2, Wembley
Description: At peak hour traffic gets banked back from exit at Powis Street to nearly all the way back to Leederville. The cars at the Powis St lights that are turning right block cars exiting from the freeway and from turning left. It can be difficult to merge given the different speeds in the lanes.  Cars constantly stop and start on the freeway with other cars going at speed trying to merge into a gap.

Name: Powis St, Glendalough

I have seen some drivers abusing each other trying to do this, and they can often block the left lane trying to merge into the right lane to go up the on-ramp.

Name: 72 & Jersey St, Wembley
Description: This interestion is subject to many near misses, swerving vehicles and people pulling in dangerously after waiting excessive times to enter Grantham Street. The intersection is heavily used as it adjoins a large primary school and Ian the road off Grantham down to the shopping centre. There is always pedestrians around the intersection and it is only a Meyer if time before a serious accident occurs unless lights are installed

Comment 1: Shree: I've witnessed many accidents at that intersection because of impatient drivers wanting to turn right or go straight. What makes it more dangerous is that there is a restaurant at that corner and a Primary school. It is not safe for pedestrians, even those walking towards the underpass as most cars don't follow speed limit and the possibility to loose control is very high
Comment 10: Suzanne : The lack of visibility at this intersection means the cars waiting to turn into Grantham St from Jersey St have to nose out into fast moving traffic before they are able to fully see the oncoming traffic. Also the wait times at this intersection can be quite long at peak periods due to only one car being allowed to cross/turn at the one time. Several accidents have occurred in the past year, the most recent crashing through the Wembley Primary School fence. Thankfully no children were nearby.
Comment 19: Gillian: This intersection is on the corner of a school and dozens of school children pass this intersection each day. I am concerned for their safely as well as the passing traffic. This is a busy intersection on a road with traffic travelling at speed with few opportunities to turn/cross at times and unfortunately some vehicles take risky actions
Comment 22: Natalie: I have seen many accidents at this intersection. It is directly next to a school and scary to watch at 830 in the morn the number of risky turns pple make.  Only a matter of time before a fatality (either in vehicle or wiping out pedestrian or pple frequently the pizza place at this intersection).  I live in the area and purposely avoid!!
Comment 23: Sandra: Major school crossing and you can�۪t see the traffic turning from Grantham into Jersey.
Comment 24: Helen: It is a registered black spot.  Numerous accidents.  Bus stop close.  Grantham is a busy road. Right next door to a school
Comment 27: So many accidents here and a cafe is now very popular with outside dining I worry a car will collide into people whilst eating. If the intersection can�۪t be modified then at least need some bollards to protect the Diners
Comment 35: Lots of accidents, people in Jersery St are impatient/poor visibility and they take risks to cross over and turn, only to cause accidents.  Lots of near misses with cars and pedestrians.
Comment 36: Kylie-Anne: MVA are high and as it is right next to a school/ pre primary and kindy it makes it a higher risk. Been a problem for a long time. Really needs improvement for the safety of all.
Comment 37: Sebastian: Traffic on Cambridge is busy both ways so it is very difficult to turn onto it from Jersey St. Lost count the number of times there has been an accident here.
Comment 38: Susan: There have been many accidents at this intersection over the years. I have been in the area for 14 years and it is an ongoing problem. There is a primary school playground on one corner of the intersection and al fresco dining on the opposite corner.
Comment 42: Stephanie: Grantham St and Jersey.  So many cars trying to turn or go straight.  Dangerous as also a school zone.
Comment 44: Several accidents, several near misses. Cars pulling out onto Grantham St when unsafe to do so due to being frustrated by waiting for safe opportunity. Residential brick wall limits visibility. School and cyclist traffic adds to the burden on this intersection.
Comment 45: Gemma : So many near misses and a few actual accidents. This is a VERY busy intersection especially at school times and no time to turn or drive across Jersey Street.
Comment 46: Accidents every few months. There is a school and very busy and popular pizza place right at the intersection. Pedestrians will get hurt
Comment 48: There are accidents at this intersection on a weekly basis.. it is beside the primary school and the last accident resulted in the vehicle going through the school fence onto the oval.
Comment 49: Sam: Accident black spot. It is only time when a fatality will happen at this intersection. Either a car will hit alfresco diners or a car will run into school fencing as has happened in November 2018
Comment 50: Richard: Cars pulling out risky, as you can be waiting for ages.
